&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An Introduction to Codal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Codal is an award-winning web design and development consultancy that helps enterprise organizations solve complex problems and accelerate growth through elegant, data-driven digital solutions. Our areas of expertise include application modernization, eCommerce, UX/UI design, product strategy, data analytics, and artificial intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Codal, you will collaborate with some of the most innovative organizations in the world and work on cutting-edge technologies that push the boundaries of design and software development. We promote long-term success, not just for our clients but for our team, helping you develop a professional roadmap that takes your career to new heights.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Codal is searching for an Accountant to manage core accounting functions, ensure the accuracy of financial reporting, and support strategic financial decisions across the organization. To ensure success, you should have extensive experience with full-cycle accounting, financial analysis, and process improvement. This role involves maintaining high quality and standards across all financial operations to support Codal&#39;s continued growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please note: this role is only open to candidates in &lt;strong&gt;Chicago and the Chicagoland area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Prepare and review monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements in accordance with GAAP, ensuring accuracy, completeness, and timeliness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Ledger Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the full-cycle accounting process, including journal entries, accounts payable, accounts receivable, and account reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month-End &amp;amp; Year-End Close:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead close processes, performing variance analysis, and resolving discrepancies to deliver clean, reliable financials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budgeting &amp;amp; Forecasting:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with leadership to develop budgets, financial plans, and ad hoc reports to support data-driven decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and refine accounting policies, procedures, and internal controls to drive operational efficiency and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration and Vendor Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate globally with our outside financial team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Ideal Candidate Skills&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;3+ years of progressive, hands-on accounting experience with increasing responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Prior experience working in an agency or professional services environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong command of GAAP and accounting best practices; experience with project-based accounting or revenue recognition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Hands-on experience with QuickBooks, ERP platforms Sage, Brex, and Bill.com; advanced Excel skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven ability to identify financial trends, resolve discrepancies, and translate data into actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standards:&lt;/strong&gt; Commitment to maintaining high standards of accuracy, compliance, and financial integrity across all deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Tax:&lt;/strong&gt; Awareness of federal, state, and local tax regulations; assist with tax preparation, filings, and audit support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Edu

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An Introduction to Codal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Codal is an award-winning web design and development consultancy that helps enterprise organizations solve complex problems and accelerate growth through elegant, data-driven digital solutions. Our areas of expertise include application modernization, eCommerce, UX/UI design, product strategy, data analytics, and artificial intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Codal, you will collaborate with some of the most innovative organizations in the world and work on cutting-edge technologies that push the boundaries of design and software development. We promote long-term success, not just for our clients but for our team, helping you develop a professional roadmap that takes your career to new heights.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you’ll be working with:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We ideate, create, and coordinate. We analyze, strategize, organize, and prioritize. We bridge the communication channel between the client and our project team. We chart the course and navigate the product roadmap sprint by sprint. Some of us are product owners. Some of us are scrum masters. Many of us wear multiple hats and do whatever’s needed to deliver successful projects.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please note this role is in our Chicago office, 3 days per week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product &amp;amp; Consulting Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with discovery, strategy, and visioning activities for prospective and existing clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support creation of proposals, statements of work, presentations, feature lists, and other client-facing deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market, competitor, vendor, and industry research to inform client recommendations and business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with workshop preparation, documentation, note-taking, and follow-up actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain Miro boards, planning materials, and workshop artifacts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PMO &amp;amp; Delivery Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with department leadership to plan, track, and drive quarterly objectives and key results (OKRs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with leadership reviews by compiling project health indicators, escalations, staffing needs, and action items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement initiatives across project delivery processes and reporting frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workforce Planning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate candidate interview scheduling and recruiting activities within the PMO department on an as needed basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support summer internship program planning, onboarding, coordination, and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Operations to assist with contractor and vendor sourcing activities, including research, coordination, and onboarding support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive &amp;amp; Organizational Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate leadership meetings, department forums, workshops, and strategic planning sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the growth and ongoing success of a selected set of strategic partnerships by coordinating meetings, tracking action items, and facilitating collaboration opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare meeting agendas, documentation, action items, and executive summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with company initiatives, offsites, team events, internship programs, and philanthropic activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support special initiatives related to AI adoption, organizational transformation, delivery excellence, and operational maturity.&lt;/li&gt;
